00:45:06,225 --> 00:45:09,569
you haven't said yes, so they want to hire you and retain you.

791
00:45:09,569 --> 00:45:14,133
But the challenge is is that she is an assistant art director and

792
00:45:14,133 --> 00:45:16,435
the art director who is in charge of her is

793
00:45:17,037 --> 00:45:23,904
left the company. And so now her title has changed, but they haven't had any talks about

794
00:45:23,904 --> 00:45:30,290
how her pay will change. And now she believes that she's getting severely underpaid. Perhaps

795
00:45:30,290 --> 00:45:35,896
that person got double what she is currently making. And it's also a complicated situation

796
00:45:35,896 --> 00:45:41,802
because when she first joined, she was the only woman in her entire department.

797
00:45:42,195 --> 00:45:44,336
And even now, there aren't that many women.

798
00:45:44,336 --> 00:45:48,479
And so she's struggling to figure out how she can negotiate and advocate

799
00:45:48,479 --> 00:45:52,122
for herself, even though she's already at the company and is very thankful

800
00:45:52,122 --> 00:45:57,446
for the job while navigating the interesting perception of women

801
00:45:57,446 --> 00:45:58,687
negotiating versus men.

802
00:45:59,602 --> 00:46:03,686
