810
00:46:35,969 --> 00:46:38,650
What do you think? Is my research correct on this?

811
00:46:39,617 --> 00:46:44,658
One particular thing I'd add there, especially for any time when you are kind of at a company and it's not clear,

812
00:46:44,658 --> 00:46:47,539
it's a promotion, it's that you're taking over another responsibility,

813
00:46:47,539 --> 00:46:52,300
make sure that you don't hinge your salary negotiation on a percentage based on your existing one.

814
00:46:52,300 --> 00:46:57,141
Because if you're taking a new role, new responsibility, it's not based on, oh, you know, we, every promotion is 10% or

815
00:46:57,141 --> 00:47:01,482
whatever it might be. Make sure you start over, reset the expectation based on market value.

816
00:47:01,482 --> 00:47:08,604
I would also say just briefly, your friend should set some time frame in her mind, at which point this is no longer

817
00:47:08,604 --> 00:47:09,384
acceptable.

818
00:47:10,052 --> 00:47:16,903
and be looking for other roles because I almost guarantee she will find more money outside of the company.

819
00:47:16,903 --> 00:47:20,850
Unfortunately, that's my experience.

