00:48:22,111 --> 00:48:23,993
that are sort of looking for their first role

835
00:48:23,993 --> 00:48:24,973
in the game industry.

836
00:48:26,444 --> 00:48:33,531
A lot of times people will go in and they'll read very generic salary negotiation tactics online

837
00:48:33,531 --> 00:48:38,056
that are actually much more sort of tailored to people who are in the middle of their career.

838
00:48:38,056 --> 00:48:41,058
So if somebody was coming, for example, right out of school...

839
00:48:41,596 --> 00:48:46,538
and decided to ask for a whole bunch more than what we offered them.

840
00:48:46,538 --> 00:48:48,818
And my first question would be why.

841
00:48:48,818 --> 00:48:50,599
And there could be a very good reason for that.

842
00:48:50,599 --> 00:48:56,661
Maybe they have experience that would actually make them really valuable.

843
00:48:56,661 --> 00:48:58,441
But oftentimes the response is,

844
00:48:58,441 --> 00:49:03,283
well, you know, for my unique skills and my unique experience.

845
00:49:04,497 --> 00:49:07,419
to which I would say, okay, what are those?

846
00:49:07,419 --> 00:49:09,300
Especially if you just came from school,

847
00:49:09,300 --> 00:49:11,701
unless you've done some really special,

848
00:49:11,701 --> 00:49:14,023
really unique things while you were there,

849
00:49:14,023 --> 00:49:18,626
you don't necessarily have unique skills or experience yet.

850
00:49:18,626 --> 00:49:23,229
So part of it is knowing that you are making an argument

851
00:49:23,229 --> 00:49:25,530
to hire you specifically,

852
00:49:25,530 --> 00:49:27,511
and you should have really concrete examples

853
00:49:27,511 --> 00:49:30,793
of why you specifically are worth what you're asking for.

854
00:49:32,040 --> 00:49:37,364
I think specifically for kind of early career folks, something that I always find really

855
00:49:37,364 --> 00:49:41,327
powerful is acknowledgement and confidence in the skills that you're bringing, but also

856
00:49:41,327 --> 00:49:44,149
really open mind to what you could be learning there, right?

857
00:49:44,149 --> 00:49:46,951
So saying things like, oh, you know, I'm excited to bring my skills here.

858
00:49:46,951 --> 00:49:50,154
And I'm really excited to learn from this team that has worked on this game or on this

859
00:49:50,154 --> 00:49:51,154
product for a while.

860
00:49:51,154 --> 00:49:55,358
That open mindedness and that ability to learn is something that I know we screened for a

861
00:49:55,358 --> 00:49:56,999
lot in our early candidates.

